            "why": "This flight demonstrates the high-stakes, rapid development cycle in private space exploration, where iterative testing, even with previous failures, is critical for ambitious goals like lunar missions and commercial viability through an IPO. The pressure from NASA's timelines and competition with Jeff Bezos' Blue Origin highlights the intense race in the space industry."
