        {
          "id": "tech-14",
          "title": "Domain Knowledge Is the Leverage",
          "link": "https://log.beshr.com/domain-knowledge-is-the-leverage/",
          "source": "Beshr Kayali Reinholdsson",
          "tags": [
            "ai",
            "backend",
            "software-development",
            "llm"
          ],
          "description": "It is becoming apparent that understanding the domain and how it connects to the program is valuable, which is why spec-driven development is now in the spotlight.",
          "one-liner": "With AI agents now capable of micro-level coding, understanding domain knowledge and system architecture is becoming the most valuable skill for human developers, driving a resurgence in spec-driven development.",
          "summary": {
            "what": "The article argues that AI agents can quickly implement code, making micro-level refactoring less impactful for human developers. Instead, the ability to understand domain knowledge, define clear interfaces, modular boundaries, dependencies, and constraints – essentially, maintain the overall system shape – is now paramount. This shift spotlights spec-driven development and emphasizes the need for good tests.",
            "why": "This suggests a fundamental re-evaluation of developer roles in an AI-assisted future, where strategic architectural thinking and domain expertise become core competencies, while AI handles lower-level implementation details.",
            "takeaway": "Focus on honing your domain knowledge and skills in defining system architecture and clear specifications, as these will provide significant leverage when working with AI coding agents."
          },
          "deep-summary": "* AI agents excel at micro-level coding tasks, such as implementing a single function or refactoring small pieces of code.\n* This diminishes the leverage of human developers who focus solely on these granular implementation details.\n* The critical skill for human developers is now understanding the domain and how it connects to the program's overall structure.\n* This includes defining modular boundaries, clear interfaces, dependencies, and constraints.\n* Spec-driven development is gaining renewed interest as a way to capture these high-level decisions for both human and AI understanding.\n* Specs should be concise and actionable, not lengthy, unread documentation.\n* Good tests are more crucial than ever to verify the output of powerful code-generating tools.\n* The insights that matter come from small experiments, not just taking claims (including AI's) at face value.\n* The principles of test-driven development, advocated for 25 years, are proving essential for working with AI agents.",
          "decoder": "* **Spec-driven development**: A software development methodology where detailed specifications (specs) of system behavior, interfaces, and constraints are defined upfront and used to guide development and verify implementation.",
          "rating": 5,
          "content-template-path": "full-content/2026-05-18/tech-14"
        }
      ]
    },
